      "description": "Available is a driver-focused Mazda RX-7 FD featuring the legendary 13B-REW twin-rotor engine. This unit retains its sophisticated sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, providing a seamless transition between the primary and secondary turbines. The chassis geometry is preserved with factory double-wishbone suspension and a rigid powerplant frame, maintaining the iconic 50/50 weight distribution. Significant mechanical updates include a high-capacity aluminum radiator for improved thermal management and a simplified vacuum line assembly to enhance boost reliability. The five-speed manual transmission is paired with a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring precise torque vectoring through the corners. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with a well-enjoyed enthusiast vehicle, the powertrain remains robust with consistent compression across both rotors. This is a mechanically sound, analog performance machine optimized for the street.",
